name: Gate Pose Variation Arm Extended on Side

muscles.name: Obliques
muscles.description:
The obliques are made up of the internal and external obliques. 

The internal oblique sits between the transverse abdominis and the external oblique. The origin is from the iliac crest, and the lower part of the pelvis. The insertion is at the linea alba, pubic crest, and the lower 3-4 ribs.

The internal oblique serves the exact same functions as the external oblique - aiding rotation, flexion and lateral flexion of the spine.

The external oblique is visible at low body fat percentages. The muscle appears as a series of diagonal lines connecting to the six-pack.

The external oblique originates from the 5th – 8th ribs, and insert at several points (linea alba, iliac spine, pubic crest, and the iliac crest).

The functions of the external oblique are to aid in rotation (chopping down a tree), flexion (bending over), and lateral flexion of the spine (bending to the side).

force.name: Hold
force.description: Exercise which resists movement as opposed to inducing.

correct_steps.text: Start on your knees and extend your right leg out to the side.
Raise your right arm above your head and reach towards the left side of the room.
Gently bend your body to the left side and rest your left hand on your left thigh.
Look up towards your right hand and hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.

correct_steps.text: Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you.
Bend your right knee and bring your heel towards your perineum.
Place your left hand on the outside of your right knee and twist your body to the right.
Reach your right hand towards your left foot and look up towards the ceiling. Hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.

mechanic.name: Isolation
mechanic.description: Exercise trains a single body part.

correct_steps.text: Sit comfortably on the floor with your legs crossed.
Inhale and raise your right arm above your head.
As you exhale, bend your body to the left side and rest your left hand on the ground.
Look up towards the ceiling and hold the pose for a few breaths. Then switch sides and repeat the pose on the other side.

correct_steps.text: Lie down on your back with your arms stretched out to your sides.
Bend your right knee and bring it towards your chest.
Slowly twist your body to the left side, bringing your right knee across your body towards the ground on the left side.
Look towards your right hand and hold the pose for a few breaths before switching sides.
